NAME
    convert-a-font

DESCRIPTION
    Convert any standard font format to any/other desired formats, including:
        - .eot
        - .woff2
        - .woff
        - .otf
        - .ttf
        - .svg

    This function requires 2 parameter(s)...
        @1 = Input font file/path (to be converted)
        @2 = Font types separated by commas (ttf,otf,eot,svg,woff,woff2)
             [leave blank then press enter for all]


SYNOPSIS
    convert-a-font PARAM_1 [PARAM_2] # brackets [] indicate optional

EXAMPLES
    convert-a-font  # For interactive script
    convert-a-font ./font.ttf otf,eot,svg  # Convert ttf to: otf, eot, svg
    convert-a-font ~/Fonts/fontname.woff2 --all # Convert woff2 file to all formats

AVAILABLE OPTIONS:
    -a, --all  [convert to all formats]
    -h, --help [show this help documentation]